value.title: Trump told a crowd of nearly all white supporters that they have 'good genes'
value.excerpt: Trump has previously suggested that he has superior genes and expressed pride in his "German blood."

value.title: Stoking his base, Trump warns of a Kamala Harris presidency

value.title: Rank-and-file union members snub Biden for Trump
value.excerpt: In some unions, especially the building trades, support for the president remains solid despite the efforts of labor leaders to convince members otherwise.

value.title: Trump and Barr call NYC an 'anarchist jurisdiction' in brazen ploy to crush dissent
value.excerpt: Everything old is new again, and a glance back at 1886 proves there is a very bloody precedent for what Trump's White House is doing here.

value.title: Voter Registration Day, Trump's UN address, Tropical Storm Beta: 5 things to know Tuesday
value.excerpt: This is a good day to register to vote, President Trump's U.N. address will be released before his latest rally and more news to start your Tuesday.

value.title: Longtime ally to Trump's postal chief was paid by RNC
value.excerpt: A former executive who worked in the private sector for Postmaster General Louis DeJoy is now on the payroll of President Donald Trump’s reelection effort

value.title: GOP House candidate Kim Klacik claims voters with ‘Trump syndrome’ won’t admit support for her ‘out loud’
value.excerpt: Maryland GOP congressional candidate Kim Klacik’s campaign has caught fire with the help of her viral ads, but many of her would-be constituents are reluctant to outwardly show their support, she told “Hannity” Monday night.

value.title: Trump applauds poll showing 45 percent support among gay men
value.excerpt: The poll, conducted by the gay social network Hornet, includes 1,200 responses from American gay men. Trump trailed Biden by 6 percent.

value.title: GOP speaker tried to urge Trump crowd to wear masks. See how it went
value.excerpt: Ohio Lt. Governor Jon Husted was booed while speaking at a Trump rally for encouraging the President's supporters to wear masks.

value.title: Betsy DeVos is under investigation for potentially violating the Hatch Act when she slammed Joe Biden in a Fox News interview
value.excerpt: "Today he's turned his back on the kids ... in favor of the teachers union ... and what they have to demand and it's really shameful," DeVos said.

value.title: Former Mueller prosecutor says the special counsel let down the public and describes Trump as 'an animal' in new book
value.excerpt: Asked whether Mueller had let down the American public, Andrew Weissmann told The Atlantic: "Absolutely, yep."

value.title: Klobuchar mocked for tweet inadvertently arguing Trump should fill SCOTUS vacancy
value.excerpt: Sen. Amy Klobuchar, D-Minn., is facing a bit of mockery over a tweet that inadvertently supports President Trump to fill the vacant Supreme Court seat.

value.title: Joe Biden looks to expand election battleground into Trump country
value.excerpt: Joe Biden’s campaign is inching into Trump country, putting money behind new ads in Iowa and Georgia as it seeks to expand the battleground map and lift Democratic candidates in the battle for the Senate.

value.title: Trump: ‘I’m so angry at Republicans’
value.excerpt: The president says his fellow Republicans have let him it down when it comes to investigating Obama and the Bidens.

value.title: Biden makes class-focused pitch to White voters in Wisconsin
value.excerpt: Joe Biden is making a bid to win back White working-class voters around smaller cities and towns in the Upper Midwest from President Donald Trump, targeting them with a cultural and economic pitch that was on display Monday in Wisconsin.

value.title: West Michigan man says yard signs were stolen. So he put up Joe Biden freeway billboards.
value.excerpt: Marshall Stern, a Democrat who lives in Newaygo County, started a GoFundMe for a billboard supporting Joe Biden's presidential campaign.

value.title: Senate should be able to move 'swiftly' on Trump pick to replace RBG: Carrie Severino
value.excerpt: The Senate should be able to move "swiftly" if either Judge Amy Coney Barrett or Judge Barbara Lagoa are nominated for the Supreme Court by President Trump, Judicial Crisis Network President Carrie Severino told "Special Report" Monday.

value.title: 2020 Daily Trail Markers: Pence says Trump is "anxious" to move forward with SCOTUS nominee process
value.excerpt: In an interview with CBS Evening News anchor and managing editor Norah O'Donnell, Vice President Mike Pence said President Trump's Supreme Court nominee will be announced by the end of the week, adding that the president "is anxious to move the process forward.

value.title: Trump must watch his language to get Americans behind SCOTUS choice, Frank Luntz says
value.excerpt: 'Framing, context is everything over these last 40 days' of the campaign, pollster tells Neil Cavuto

value.title: Biden marks grim coronavirus milestone, says ‘Trump panicked’ on pandemic
value.excerpt: As the national death toll from the coronavirus pandemic passes 200,000 people, Democratic presidential nominee Joe Biden cautioned that Americans must avoid “becoming numb to the toll that is taken.”

value.title: Biden refuses to say whether he'd expand the Supreme Court if he wins
value.excerpt: The non-answer marked a rhetorical shift for the Democratic nominee, who has opposed the "court-packing" idea in the past.

value.title: Biden's once maligned digital operation raises big money by embodying candidate
value.excerpt: When Rob Flaherty began describing Joe Biden's digital strategy as a "battle for the soul of the Internet" earlier this year, the Democratic primary had barely ended, the former vice president's campaign was alarmingly low on money and President Donald Trump's digital-centric campaign looked like a juggernaut.
